Mobil Corp said it will spend over 30mln dlrs to upgrade a gasoline-producing unit at its Beaumont,Texas, refinery.    It said the unit is a catalytic reformer, which convertslow-octane components of gasoline into high-octane componentsfor use in Super Unleaded gasoline.    The company said the modernization will allow the unit toregenerate catalysts on a continuous basis without shutdown.Currently, it must be shut twice a year.  The unit produces46,000 barrels of gasoline components a year.  Constructionwill start late this year, with completion set for mid-1989. Reuter&#3;